The paper deals with the design and construction of Space-Time Block Codes (STBCs), which is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of Clifford algebras in constructing these codes, which is a topic in Symbolic Data Analysis (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper presents simulation results, which falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves mathematical optimization and construction techniques, which could fall under Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) or Machine Learning (cs.LG).
